   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can approve a pending user account registration for non-Active Directory users.  After approving the pending account, you will need to access the user account and assign roles to the new user. </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the module menu, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Administration</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the navigation pane, expand <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">User Management</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Pending Registrations</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">PENDING REGISTRATIONS LIST</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the required user registration request to approve.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Approve</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">A confirmation message is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">OK</uicontrol>. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The user is added to the application database. You can view the user account in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">USER ACCOUNTS</uicontrol> page. <note class="- topic/note "> The approved user accounts require the Administrator to define the user details, roles, and business units. </note>
               <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For information on accessing the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">USER ACCOUNTS</uicontrol> page, refer to<xref href="../../../CoSP/Administration/User_Management/User_Accounts/UserAccs.dita"
                        class="- topic/xref ">User Accounts</xref>.</ph>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
